tributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe book contains a number of studies in Japanese phonology and morphology, all analyses by leading scholars in the field. It presents an overview of the work that has been done in Japan and other countries and offers new solutions to long-standing problems. In the phonology chapters, it focuses on segmental as well as suprasegmental issues, including voicing and tone, approaching these issues from a variety of perspectives, including Optimality Theory and Government Phonology. In the morphology chapters, attention is given to truncation patterns and the possibilities for compound formation.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aJapanese languagexMorphology. 0aJapanese languagexPhonology. 4aMorphologie. 4aPhonologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAkasaka, Yukiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFukazawa, Haruka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaraguchi, Shosuke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonma, Takeru, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKageyama, Taro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitahara, Mafuyu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKubozono, Haruo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasuya, Yosihiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNamiki, Takayasu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNanjo, Kensuke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNishihara, Tetsuo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.